text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!SignLanguage]]%0a%0a!Non-Manual Markers in ASL%0a%0a:Author: AlexisA%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aNon-manual markers, like facial expression and body position, are used in ASL to indicate emotion, questioning, and adjectives/adverbs.%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIt is a common misconception outside of the deaf community that ASL is spoken entirely with a person's hands. In reality, non-manual markers, such as facial expression, head and shoulder movements, and body position, play a key role in communicating the speaker's message.%0a%0aFacial expressions can be used to signify adverbs or adjectives that modify the word being signed simultaneously. For instance, squinting the eyes and tightening the mouth means "in tiny increments" and is used to modify verbs like increase or decrease. Facial expressions can also indicate grammatical structures: speakers will raise their eyebrows and widen their eyes in conditional clauses, for example.%0a%0aBody positions can also signify grammatical structures. When signing "a or b," the speaker will often shift their weight in one direction when signing things related to a and the other direction for things related to b in order to communicate more clearly.%0a%0aAlso note that many of these characteristics are common across many different sign languages. I've chosen to focus on ASL here to avoid painting with too broad a brush.%0a%0aSources:%0ahttps://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/11/why-great-sign-language-interpreters-are-so-animated/264459/%0a%0ahttps://www.lifeprint.com/asl101/pages-layout/facialexpressions.htm%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: A:)%0a(:Category: SignLanguage:)
